  "doc_id": "20498",
  "text": "A zero-point shear strain ∂u y /∂z ≃ k m U zpf , where k m and U zpf represent a wavenumber and an amplitude of the zero-point motion of the SAW, is experimentally obtained along with the equations (1) and (2). Using the SAW wavelength of λ SAW = 40 µm, we finally find U zpf = 0.5 × 10 −2 fm, while a theoretical estimation derived from a value reported in [CITATION_1] , along with the effective mode area of the SAW resonator of π × 100 µm × 110 µm, yields U zpf = 1 × 10 −2 fm. The theoretical value is compatible with the experimentally estimated value, taking into account a large uncertainty accompanied by the calibration of N SAW .",
